:textile
  Hello, this is an extremely preliminary PBCore validator. It can detect certain types of errors and deviations from "best practices" in <a href="http://www.pbcore.org/">PBCore</a> records.

  For more information, see <a href="http://vermicel.li/blog/2009/02/02/introducing-the-pbcore-validator.html">the blog post introducing the validator</a>.

%h2 Validate a document
%form{ :action => "/validator", :method => "post", :enctype => "multipart/form-data" }
  %p
    %label{ :for => "file" } Select a file to validate:
    %input{ :id => "file", :name => "file", :type => "file" }
  %p
    %label{ :for => "textarea" } <strong>or</strong> paste a PBCore document into the textbox:
    %br
    %textarea{ :id => "textarea", :name => "textarea", :rows => 5, :cols => 80 }
  %p
    %label{ :for => "version" } PBCore Version:
    %select{ :name => "version", :id => "version" }
      - Validator::PBCORE_VERSIONS.sort.each do |code, version|
        %option{ :value => code, :selected => (code == "1.2") }&= version[:version]
    %label{ :for => "vocabs" } Controlled Vocabularies
    %input{ :type => "checkbox", :name => "vocabs" }
    %label{ :for => "best_practices" } Best Practices
    %input{ :type => "checkbox", :name => "best_practices" }
  %p
    %input{ :type => "reset", :value => "Clear Form" }
    %input.s{ :type => "submit", :value => "Validate PBCore" }

%hr

